Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for four (4) years.
Conditions of probation:
1) maintain fulltime employment, schooling or combination;
2) Pay court costs of $518.00;
3) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
4) pay restitution of $24.00 to the Crime Victim Compensation Program;
5) spend nine (9) months in the county jail, under the Huber Law, commencing on 06-23-15 by 6:00 p.m.  Court authorizes release not only for employment purposes but also for involvement in child care as found appropriate by the agent.  Court further orders transfer to either Calumet, Outagamie or Winnebago county jail;
6) additional three (3) months in the county jail, under the Huber Law, stayed and to be imposed at the agents discretion and upon order of the court;
7) complete parenting classes;
8) have no contact with the victim until authorized by his agent;
9) defendant is to comply with all family court requirements;
10) assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process.
There is $7,500.00 cash bail on file.  The Court orders that $518.00 be used to pay the court costs; $24.00 be used to pay the restitution and the balance of $6,958.00 be returned to Christine Matz by check instruction no: CR 74. 
Photographs of changing table.
Minutes.
